-- 
Amtrak Derailment Means New Jersey Transit Trains Face 30 Minute Delays

-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 
2011-08-11T21:22:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/new-jersey-transit-says-some-trains-leaving-new-york-face-30-minute-delays.html
New Jersey Transit  said certain
trains leaving  New York  City face delays as long as 30 minutes
and some trains may be canceled or combined, after an Amtrak
train derailed.  Northeast Corridor, North Jersey Coast Line and Midtown
Direct trains are subject to delays of 20 minutes to 30 minutes,
the agency said in an e-mailed statement.  Amtrak said customers should expect 10 minute to 20 minute
delays into and out of New York. The derailment occurred at its
maintenance yard in Sunnyside, Queens, Amtrak said in a separate
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Chang in San Francisco at 
